[The occurrence of this confirmed human MVE virus infection case
occurred at the same time that the virus was detected in birds in this
area of South Australia (see ProMED-mail archive number
20110330.0989). The recent unusually heavy rains and flooding in the
state have created breeding sites for mosquito vectors. One hopes that
people residing in these areas of South Australia will heed advice of
health authorities to avoid mosquito bites, as that is the only
preventive measure available.

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map showing the location of South
Australia state can be accessed at <http://healthmap.org/r/00N_>. -
